summary: The End of the Line
body:
The End of the Line

Marvel Secret Wars Battleworld (I think I got that right) 1872 AU.

You’re stupid if you think Tony Stark ever stopped inventing. Did he run away after the war? Hell yes. He settled in the rowdiest and most ridiculous one-horse town he could find. Made himself right at home, he did. Nobody asked what he was doing there and he never answered when they tried. Timely had far too many strange characters of their own to bother with the washed up weaponsmith that no one had seen in three years. He would know. He’s met some of them before.

Fuck you if you think he ever made anything close to another revolver. Fuck you, your family, and the horse you rode in on. Because he didn’t. It took him a year in Timely before he could even think about the scene without throwing up wherever he was, and by then he’d had everyone fooled well enough that they didn’t question it. Who would? He was drunk.

God-Doom should chop you into tiny bits and feed you to his demon dogs if you thought Tony Stark didn’t know how to use every single weapon in his arsenal, half of them hand-crafted by the man himself. There were three people who dared to go to his house when the chimney smoked for too long or the echoing gunshots woke some of the townsfolk. The deputy would always leave first, but his wife and Sheriff Rogers would stay well into the evening, and if Rogers stuck around longer than most, no one breathed a word of it.

You’ve lost your wits if you believe anything Wilson Fisk and his cronies spout, but Steve’s had enough. Enough of the corruption and lies, of trying to standup for what was right. There were one too many people dying of unnatural causes around here, and he’d had enough of not having answers. Letting Red Wolf go was the last straw and, well, the powder keg went sky high.

People will spit on your grave if you ever say that Tony Stark didn’t save Sheriff Rogers’ life. Whatever strange cloth Rogers was wearing under his vest, it stopped bullets. Even if the sheriff flew backwards and jerked around. Was he bleeding? Yes. But his hand twitched as the pigs came to feast, and while Tony snarled and took on Fisk’s men, the citizens of Timely quietly fished Rogers out of the trough. Dead or not, he deserved a proper send off.

You’re blinder than the old Daredevil of Hell’s Kitchen if you didn’t see the look of pure agony on Stark’s face. Bottle cast aside, he raised his hand and fired. Click-Boom. Click-Boom. Click-Boom. He wasn’t the only one to shoot at Fisk’s men, but he sure was the last thing they saw.

No one would blame you if you gaped openly at the sight of Natasha Barnes knocking heads around a few days later. She’s a sight to behold, and some say her husband trained her in the dead of night, between the gunshots and the fall of Stark’s hammer. Either way, she gets her job done.

You would be played for a fool if you ever asked Sheriff Rogers how he survived. Tony Stark would laugh and clap you on the back. Say it was a miracle, of course, now have another drink, Peter. The knowing gleam in his eyes and the amused look on Rogers’ face made you shelve it aside, for more sober times.

######################################################################

Late one night, you’re on the roof staring at the stars. The muted voices are familiar, and you dare not to listen in. You do anyway.

“Why can’t you let this go?” Missus Barnes demanded.

“Because, darling,” Stark’s smooth drawl was easy on anyone’s ears, super hearing or not. “I’m an inventor. We tend to invent.”

“She’s right, Tony. This is getting out of hand.” Banner, of all people. “What makes you think Fisk will so hell-bent on coming after Timely?”

“I know a sore loser when I see one, and trust me, they don’t go down easy.” Stark muttered darkly. A shifting of fabric told him that someone flinched, and the unusually quiet voice confirmed who it was.

“That they don’t.” Missus Barnes seemed rather sure of both statements. “But you’ve done enough, Anthony. Surely you can rest easier?”

Something shattered against a wall.

“It wasn’t enough!” Stark roared. “But it will be.” He insisted firmly.

Blood pumped quickly through their bodies and the scent of fear tinged the air around them.

They’re preparing for war…

The newsboy crept down from his roof and back into his room, feigning sleep when his aunt came to check on him.

Maybe they could use a few extra hands.

body:
Pairings: Tony x reader, MJ x Peter?

Warnings: none

Time: post ca:cw, iw doesn’t exist

Summary: the rogue avengers come, after being gone for a year, to the avengers facility.



“Hi guys welcome back” you greet the avengers. After the whole civil war, half the avengers became fugitives. They’ve been on the run for almost 2 years when Tony foubnd a way to clear their names. 

“Y/n, god it’s so good to see you again” Natasha hugs you. “I missed you so much Nat” you hug her back. “Hey Steve” you walk up to him to give him a hug. “Y/n, how’ve you been?” he asks. “Y’know good. I had some amnesia after the fight, and ended in the hospital but all is well now” you smile at him. “Wait did you say amnesia?” Sam asks you. “Yeah” you scratch the back of your head, “it was noting really” you give a timid smile before giving him a hug as well. 

“Where is the rest?” Steve aks. “Oh,, Tony is probably in his lab. Rhodey is with his family, Clint is a the farm and Wanda and Vision should get here any moment” you say. “Wait did you just say Rhodey has a family?” Natasha questions. “Oh yes he met this cute doctor at the hospital, 2 years later they’re expecting a baby girl. Do you guys want anything to drink?” you ask. “Yes coffee please” they all say at the same time. “So I take it that you haven’t had a decent cup since you left” you snicker. “You could ay that yes” Sam responses. 

You start making the hot beverages. “Misses Stark, mister Stark required your assistance in the lab” FRIDAY announces. “Oh better get going. I’ll see you in a bit” you quirp.

“Did FRIDAY just say misses Stark?” Sam looks bewilderd to his teammates. “Yeah, she did” Steve confirms. They all stare at where you just left the door. A lot must’ve happend while they were gone.”



“hey baby what’s wrong?” you chirp as you set foot in the well known lab. “Nothin” he humms. “Then why did you call me?” you raise your eyebrows. “What can’t I just wanna spend time with you” he gives you a smirk. “No you cannot and are you coming?” you rub his back. “Where to?” he looks at you confused. “You remember? the others are back” you smile. “Was that today?” he asks at which you nod your head. “Oh god, I forgot about it” he sighs. “Okay first of you can call me Y/n, and second of all it doesn’t matter honey” you kiss his forehead. “Misses Starks it seems as Wanda and Vison are back as well” Friday states. “I gotta go, I’ll see you there” you wave goodbye ath him and walk back towards the common room. 

“Wanda, Vision it’s so good to have you back” you hug them, “How was Scottland?” “Scottland was fantastic, we had so much fun” Wanda smiles at Vision. “That’s great to hear why don’t you sit down with the rest while I grab you something to drink” you point at the rest. They walk towards the rest to see them widely discussing something. 

“Guys what are you whispering about?” Wanda asks. “FRIDAY called Y/n Misses Stark” Natasha says. “She did what?!” Wanda screams. “Wanda, dear, I think Y/n will hear you if you scream that loud” Vision says to his girlfriend. “oh right, thanks Vis” Wanda pecks him on the cheek. 

“Here you go” you walk in with two drinks in you hand, “What’s wrong?” you furrow your eyebrows. “Nothin’” Wanda quipps. “Alright” you squint your eyes not believing a word she says. “How is you memory Y/n? last tinme we saw you didn’t remember anything?” Vision asks polite. “WAIT! You didn’t remember anything? I thought you said it was nothing” Natasha stands up. “Okay so it was somethin but I just didn’t want you guys to worry or feel guilty” you confess.

“God, you’re sweeter than honey” Tony says from the doorway. “Oh god, Tony” you giggle. “tsk tsk, it’s weird to talk in third person” he ‘scolds’ you, making you shake your head. “God you’re so weird” you chuckle. He pouts his lip and places his hand on his heart “god I take back what I just said you’re more bitter than black coffee” 

Everyone just kinda stares at the interaction. “What?” you ask. “It’s just, since when are you a couple?” Wanda asks. “one year, 3 months, 9 hours and 6 seconds exactly” Tony checks his watch. “Og course you know the exact time we kissed first” you shake your head. “say what you want but, you like me” he points at you. “No, it’s not like we’ve been together for a year and three months” you say sarcatically. “I love you, angel” “I love you to Tony”

At this moment the lift door opens and a certain brown haired boy steps out, “Mom dad you’re not going to believe what happend today” he says not noticing that all the avengers are on the couch except for Bruce, Thor and Clint.

“waht happend honey?” you ask him. “well, I asked MJ to homecoming and she said yes” he fist pumps the air. “God I remember MJ she is a nice girl” Tony chirpes in. “yeah,, she is” peter bites the apple, only for it to fall on the ground when he sees the avengers. “Peter these are our friends” you point at them. “Holy shit!” Peter exclaims earning a language from cap. “Mom why didn’t you say they were coming.” he whines. 

“Okay this is enough!” Sam suddenly yells. “What’s wrong Sam” you tilt your head. “I know it’s been two years, but we come back and you two are married and adopted a 14 year old?” he points at Tony, Peter and you. Tony and you exchange a look before bursting out in laughter. 

“We’re not married,,, yet” Tony says. “Yeah,, wait yet?” you say to be ignored. “And we didn’t adopt Peter he still lives with his aunt May, he’s just our spider-child and 17 years old” Tony continues.

“Wait but then why did FRIDAY call you misses Stark?” Steve asks. “It’s an old joke between us” you explain, “because someone doesn’t have the balls to aks me” you glare at Tony. Everybody chuckles. “Oh realy?”Tony raises his eyebrows. “Really” you smirk at him.

Tony lowers himslef to his knees “Y/n Y/l/n, I love you so much. When you got the amnesia I was heartbroken that you didn’t remeber me. It killed me, and I hated that that was what it took to get us together. I felt like you only loved my because I was there, and thatv when your memories would get back you would leave me. You proved me wrong. The day you said you had your memories back. You laughed your ass of that you’ve been in love with me since we first met and I have to admit it was quite funny. And that waiting so long for us to finally know how much we loved each other was worth it. So Y/n Y/l/n will you marry me?”

Fixed that one drawing of Tony in the sensory deprivation chamber. I purposefully kept him in pencil to show he feels like he’s fading away. Also his reactor is in blue since it’s the only light in the room and his tears I also colored for extra angst to make them pop more.

I drew that scene with him and the woman because I liked that scene. I only colored her eyes and hair because those are what brings his memories back the rest is black and white to show his life without his memory is stark, cold and lifeless. I realize now he’s holding the pistol wrong and I feel real dumb but now it’s in pen and I can’t change it.

Anyways working on drawing a face that looks more like Tony. Figured out I’m not good at that it’s hard because he doesn’t have his normal hairstyle or facial hair. So none of them read as Tony just look like Bucky.
